6aPIGBE","media_type":"video","release_date":"2024-03-06T17:00:00+00:00","category":"Environment","subtype":"news","column":null,"page_number":null},{"id":1048136,"contentful_id":"5uXb3Q7WYwnAw3EO0PFEKo","mura_id":"7572A355-B54E-4FFC-A982FB5A00A628C8","mura_contentid":"0C427866-0057-4365-BBCD179171834150","title":"This Astrophysicist Makes Stellar Nurseries That Fit in the Palm of Your Hand","display_title":"<p>This Astrophysicist Makes Stellar Nurseries That Fit in the Palm of Your Hand</p>","slug":"this-astrophysicist-makes-stellar-nurseries-that-fit-in-the-palm-of-your-hand","url":"/video/this-astrophysicist-makes-stellar-nurseries-that-fit-in-the-palm-of-your-hand/","summary":"<p>How artist and astrophysicist Nia Imara makes 3-D prints of the birth of stars</p>","authors":[{"mura_id":"AB480386-5A3D-4722-B12CE14420F4F9AC","url":"/author/tulika-bose/","contentful_id":"2dqn97KeFJfBF8JMz5AVff","name":"Tulika Bose","slug":"tulika-bose","biography":"<p><b>Tulika Bose</b> is senior multimedia editor at <i>Scientific American</i>.</p>","picture_file":null,"contacts":[{"type":"x","value":"@TulikaBose_"}]},{"mura_id":"87ABE4CF-5F6F-4C75-AE15297106819023","url":"/author/jason-drakeford/","contentful_id":"5Wi4a7ZtRCa1henfxSEPEv","name":"Jason Drakeford","slug":"jason-drakeford","biography":"<p><b>Jason Drakeford</b> is a documentary filmmaker, video journalist and educator telling true, impactful stories with motion graphics and cinematic visuals.</p>","picture_file":null,"contacts":[{"type":"x","value":"@jasondrakeford"}]},{"mura_id":"EAF3FDDA-8E4E-4DD1-9A24565452B7FFAD","url":"/author/kelso-harper/","contentful_id":"1zsQMJUaQLz8bYIZUsOzyC","name":"Kelso Harper","slug":"kelso-harper","biography":"<p><b>Kelso Harper</b> is an award-nominated Multimedia Editor at <i>Scientific American</i>. They produce, direct, and film short documentaries and social videos, and help produce, host, and edit SciAm's podcast Science, Quickly. They received a bachelor's in chemistry from Johns